How Does dual wield work...<br>
<br>
Primary weapon 10/20<br>
Seconday weapon 20/40<br>
<br>
now, I realize that there is a % chance that you will dual wield, but at what time does this &quot;chance&quot; occur.... is it every time you swing your primary weapon? If that were so, wouldnt the delay of the secondary weapon be pointless? You'd rather have a 23 500 damage weapon in there, because delay would be meaningless...<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, perhaps if has a %  chance of firing every time you swing your primary, but if you have dual wielded the previous round it makes sure the secondary delay time has passed? at lower levels this might make wielding a higher damage higher delay secondary weapon useful anyway, since your dual wield chance will be fairly low..<br>
<br>
<br>
anyway, if someone wants to explain this tome, i would appreciate it...<br>
